content.description: From the incut rail, climb the center of the slab.
content.location: Left of edge of the earth boulder.  Not far north of the Larry Collins bench, just below a very prominent overlook.

content.description: Start on the large jug feature near the center of the face and work straight up using small crimps and sidepulls. About halfway up, I trended to the right arete and finished up around the corner (without using the detached blocks). Staying true to the center is a project waiting to be done.
content.protection: Pads. Landing is flat, but the climb is pretty tall and intimidating
content.location:
Two Options:

 1. Hike the west bluff trail (from the north) to the first main overlook after the gully. You're standing on the topout. Located in between "By Gully" and "Pearly Gate" in the Swartling Guide.

 2. Hike directly up the bluff from Happy Go Highball

content.description: Start sitting, left hand with a low downpulling flat edge, and right with a low incut sidepull.  Climb up and left, traverse across the face through a rail, gain the other arete and top out the slab above the slanting landing.
content.location: Just below B.I.A. To the south.  Which is just below Edge of the Earth.

climbs.name: The Believer
climbs.fa: Ian CB, Kevin B and Ben S

content.description: From the edge at chest level in the middle of the pretty slab, move right, gaining a pod slot, and continue up through better holds.  Don’t use the other wall to the right.  Pretty tricky and one of those v3’s that could give you a run for your money..
content.protection: Pads, good landing and not so tall.
content.location: On the Flat Earth Boulder.  Just left of the Edge of the Earth Boulder.  First very prominent lookout if walking from the North up the West Bluff Trail as it starts to flatten out.. (ten-15 minutes probably.). Just below the trail, and a nice view of the lake.  Good landing too.  Just at the bottom of a short gully on the left.

content.description: Start on the jug.  Climb the arete and face feature.  A fun and awesome problem that stays on you until the end.
content.location: Just below Edge of the Earth.

climbs.name: Archaic Conception
climbs.fa: Maybe Ian CB, Ben S and Kevin B

content.description: Start on the edge from a stand in the middle of the pretty slab.  Move left to better holds and continue up fun moves.
content.protection: Pads.  Good landing, not so tall.
content.location: On the Flat Earth Boulder.  Just left of the Edge of the Earth Boulder.  First very prominent lookout if walking from the North up the West Bluff Trail as it starts to flatten out.. (ten-15 minutes probably.). Just below the trail, and a nice view of the lake.  Good landing too.

content.description: A collection of climbs, and a hard project at the first very prominent overlook when you crest the West Bluff to the plateau.  The climbs are below and a gully on the south side of the overlook is used to access them.
